  <mainDescription>&lt;a id=&quot;Top&quot; name=&quot;Top&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Overview&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    This tool mentor supports Designing Use Case with Rational XDE Developer - Java Platform Edition.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The steps in this tool mentor match those in the corresponding task.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Links to topics in XDE online Help are marked with &lt;img alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot; src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The following steps are performed in this tool mentor:&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li style=&quot;LIST-STYLE-TYPE: none&quot;>&#xD;
        &lt;ul>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                &lt;a href=&quot;#Describe%20Interactions%20Between%20Design%20Objects&quot;>Describe Interactions Between Design&#xD;
                Objects&lt;/a>&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                &lt;a href=&quot;#Simplify%20Sequence%20Diagrams%20Using%20Subsystems%20(optional)&quot;>Simplify Sequence Diagrams&#xD;
                Using Subsystems&lt;/a> (optional)&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                &lt;a href=&quot;#Describe%20Persistence-Related%20Behavior&quot;>Describe Persistence-Related Behavior&lt;/a>&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                &lt;a href=&quot;#Refine%20the%20Flow%20of%20Events%20Description&quot;>Refine the Flow of Events Description&lt;/a>&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                &lt;a href=&quot;#Unify%20Classes%20and%20Subsystems&quot;>Unify Design Classes and Subsystems&lt;/a>&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                &lt;a href=&quot;#Evaluate%20Your%20Results&quot;>Evaluate the Results&lt;/a>&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ul>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    &lt;a id=&quot;Describe Interactions Between Design Objects&quot; name=&quot;Describe Interactions Between Design Objects&quot;>&lt;b>Describe&#xD;
    Interactions Between Design Objects&lt;/b>&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    For each use-case realization, you should illustrate the interactions between its participating design objects by&#xD;
    creating one or more sequence diagrams. You might have created early versions of these diagrams, the analysis use-case&#xD;
    realizations, during &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot; href=&quot;./../../../core.base_rup/tasks/use_case_analysis_A6990185.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{28014615-A62F-452D-B821-30C7CAB0EC44}&quot;>Task: Use-Case Analysis&lt;/a>. These analysis use-case realizations&#xD;
    describe interactions between &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../core.base_rup/workproducts/rup_analysis_class_DAF7CE03.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{1E20603F-A5B8-42D5-BDBC-69DCE9C0FCDB}&quot;>analysis classes&lt;/a>. They must be evolved to describe interactions&#xD;
    between design elements.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    One approach is to create a new use-case realization and sequence diagrams by following these steps:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ol>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Navigate to the Design-Model package in which the new use-case realizations are to be created. See &lt;a&#xD;
        class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../../core.base_rup/guidances/whitepapers/model_structure_guidelines_for_rational_xde_developer_6D2FD64A.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;2.67081400527339E-306&quot;>Rational XDE Model Structure Guidelines&lt;/a>.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Create a use-case diagram. See &lt;img alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot; src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Adding Diagrams&lt;/i>&#xD;
        &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;rs&quot;,&quot;rs_t_add_dgm&quot;); -->.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Add the use-case realization (a collaboration instance) to the diagram. (See &lt;img alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot;&#xD;
        src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Adding Shapes to Diagrams&lt;/i> &#xD;
        &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;rs&quot;,&quot;rs_t_add_shp_dgm&quot;); -->.) Give it the&#xD;
        same name as the use case.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Drag and drop the use case that it realizes onto the diagram. See &lt;img alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot;&#xD;
        src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Adding Shapes to Diagrams&lt;/i> &#xD;
        &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;rs&quot;,&quot;rs_t_add_shp_dgm&quot;); -->.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Add a realization relationship from the use-case realization to the use case. See &lt;img alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot;&#xD;
        src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Adding Realization Relationships&lt;/i> &#xD;
        &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;rs&quot;,&quot;rs_t_add_realztn_relshp&quot;); -->.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        For each independent sub-flow (scenario) create one or more interaction instances. (In the Model Explorer,&#xD;
        right-click the collaboration instance, and then click &lt;b>Add UML &amp;gt; Interaction Instance&lt;/b>.) Consider naming&#xD;
        the interaction instance &quot;&amp;lt;use-case name&amp;gt; - &amp;lt;flow type&amp;gt;.&quot;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Create a sequence diagram for this interaction instance. See &lt;img alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot;&#xD;
        src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Adding Diagrams&lt;/i> &#xD;
        &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;rs&quot;,&quot;rs_t_add_dgm&quot;); -->.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Type a brief description of the scenario that the sequence diagram depicts. See &lt;img alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot;&#xD;
        src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Documenting Model Elements&lt;/i> &#xD;
        &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;rs&quot;,&quot;rs_t_doc_model_elem&quot;); -->.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Drag and drop actors, classes, and interfaces onto the diagram to create objects for interaction. See &lt;img&#xD;
        alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot; src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Adding Shapes to Diagrams&lt;/i> &#xD;
        &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;rs&quot;,&quot;rs_t_add_shp_dgm&quot;); -->.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Add messages between the objects. See &lt;img alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot; src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Adding&#xD;
        Messages or Stimuli&lt;/i> &#xD;
        &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;rs&quot;,&quot;rs_t_add_messages&quot;); -->.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Describe each message. See &lt;img alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot; src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Documenting Model&#xD;
        Elements&lt;/i> &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;rs&quot;,&quot;rs_t_doc_model_elem&quot;); -->.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        To describe how the object behaves when it receives the message, assign an operation to the message. See &lt;img&#xD;
        alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot; src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Assigning Operations to Messages or Stimuli&lt;/i> &#xD;
        &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;rs&quot;,&quot;rs_t_assgn_op_mess&quot;); -->.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ol>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Alternatively, if you are not maintaining a separate Analysis Model, you may decide to modify your existing sequence&#xD;
    diagrams to reflect the evolution of the design elements.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Reference: &lt;img alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot; src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Working with Interaction (Sequence)&#xD;
    Diagrams&lt;/i> &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;rs&quot;,&quot;rs_o_work_inter_dgm&quot;); -->.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    &lt;a id=&quot;Simplify Sequence Diagrams Using Subsystems (optional)&quot;&#xD;
    name=&quot;Simplify Sequence Diagrams Using Subsystems (optional)&quot;>&lt;b>Simplify Sequence Diagrams Using Subsystems&#xD;
    (optional)&lt;/b>&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    See the previous step for guidance on working with sequence diagrams.&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    &lt;a id=&quot;Describe Persistence-Related Behavior&quot; name=&quot;Describe Persistence-Related Behavior&quot;>&lt;b>Describe&#xD;
    Persistence-Related Behavior&lt;/b>&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Persistence mechanisms are ideally described using patterns. See the following topics in the Rational XDE online Help:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;img alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot; src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Rational XDE Design Patterns&lt;/i> &#xD;
        &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;ea&quot;,&quot;ea_c_xde_dsign_pttrn&quot;); -->&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;img alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot; src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Benefits of Using Patterns&lt;/i> &#xD;
        &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;ea&quot;,&quot;ea_c_benefit_pttrn&quot;); -->&#xD;
         &lt;!-- begin - wsw -->&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;img alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot; src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Understanding J2EE Pattern-Driven Development&lt;/i> &#xD;
        &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;j&quot;,&quot;jee_o_patbdev&quot;); -->&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;img alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot; src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>J2EE Pattern-Driven Development&lt;/i> &#xD;
        &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;j&quot;,&quot;jee_c_j2ee_pattrns&quot;); -->&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;img alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot; src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Supported J2EE Patterns&lt;/i> &#xD;
        &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;j&quot;,&quot;jee_o_supported_ejbs&quot;); -->&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;img alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot; src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Defining Relationships for EJBs&lt;/i> &#xD;
        &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;j&quot;,&quot;jee_o_relating_ejbs&quot;); -->&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;img alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot; src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Persistence Relationships&lt;/i> &#xD;
        &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;j&quot;,&quot;jee_r_ejb_persist_relships&quot;); -->&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;img alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot; src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Creating Persistence Relationships Between&#xD;
        EJBs&lt;/i> &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;j&quot;,&quot;jee_t_creating_ejb_rels&quot;); -->&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    &lt;a id=&quot;Refine the Flow of Events Description&quot; name=&quot;Refine the Flow of Events Description&quot;>&lt;b>Refine the Flow of Events&#xD;
    Description&lt;/b>&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Additional description can be added to the sequence diagrams for clarification. Text can be added anywhere on the&#xD;
    diagram. Notes can be added and attached to shapes on the diagram. Consider using the RUP-provided template for &lt;a&#xD;
    class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../../core.base_rup/workproducts/rup_use_case_realization_E4F713BD.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{87EB094F-095B-4981-ACC3-319B3B298641}&quot;>Work Product: Use Case Realization&lt;/a>.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Reference: &lt;img alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot; src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Attaching Notes to Shapes&lt;/i> &#xD;
    &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;rs&quot;,&quot;rs_t_attach_notes_shp&quot;); -->, &lt;img&#xD;
    alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot; src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Documenting Model Elements&lt;/i> &#xD;
    &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;rs&quot;,&quot;rs_t_doc_model_elem&quot;); -->, &lt;img&#xD;
    alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot; src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Linking External Files to Model Elements&lt;/i> &#xD;
    &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;rs&quot;,&quot;rs_t_lnk_extrn_file_mdl_ele&quot;); -->&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    &lt;a id=&quot;Unify Classes and Subsystems&quot; name=&quot;Unify Classes and Subsystems&quot;>&lt;b>Unify Design Classes and Subsystems&lt;/b>&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    As use cases are realized, you must unify the identified design classes and subsystems to ensure homogeneity and&#xD;
    consistency in the Design Model.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Part of unifying the design is identifying common patterns that can be factored out and reused. See the following&#xD;
    topics in the Rational XDE online Help:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;img alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot; src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Implementing Design Patterns&lt;/i> &#xD;
        &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;ea&quot;,&quot;ea_o_rat_xde_pttrn&quot;); -->&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;img alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot; src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Rational XDE Design Patterns&lt;/i> &#xD;
        &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;ea&quot;,&quot;ea_c_xde_dsign_pttrn&quot;); -->&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;img alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot; src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; />&lt;i>Benefits of Using Patterns&lt;/i> &#xD;
        &lt;!--  Temporarily removed Javascript - ReferenceHelpTopic(topicTitle,&quot;ea&quot;,&quot;ea_c_benefit_pttrn&quot;); -->&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    &lt;a id=&quot;Evaluate Your Results&quot; name=&quot;Evaluate Your Results&quot;>&lt;b>Evaluate the Results&lt;/b>&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    There is no Rational XDE specific guidance for this step.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
